(:summary    "Add legalese to your program files"
 :created    "2004"
 :updated    "2004"
 :license    "GPL-2"
 :authors    (("Jorgen Schaefer" . "forcer@forcix.cx"))
 :maintainer ("Jorgen Schaefer" . "forcer@forcix.cx")
 :provided   (legalese)
 :required   ((("emacs" finder)))
 :keywords   ("convenience")
 :commentary "\
This file adds the sometimes necessary legalese to your files. That
is, it adds a license header. For most files, it tries to adhere to
a nice standard layout.

I recommend the following setup:

(setq comment-style 'extra-line)
(add-hook 'scheme-mode-hook
          (lambda ()
            (set (make-local-variable 'comment-add) 1)))")
